name: hoacb
description:
This model is based on the beautiful HYC. Trigger word is hoacb. Work with all styles that I've tried so far. Always use vae-ft-mse-840000-ema-pruned. You can do eye experiments for changing her eye colors, eg: Deep Blue Eyes, Hazel Green Eyes. Play around with her hair as well, she works on Blonde, Black, Redhead and naturally is a Brunette.

For best results use Heun for sampling at 20-35 (so far tested).

CFG scale so far 9 (I use as default) have been working best.

modelVersions.name: hoacblora.safetensors
modelVersions.description:
These are LORA extract of the original hoacb.ckpt, which is a smaller alternative to the original checkpoint model. The results obtained from this LORA extract may not be as strong as the original checkpoint model, but it can be useful for those who need to save space on their hard drive.

There are two LORA models available: the hoachlora.safetensors created from 128 DIM and the hoacbLORAv2.safetensors created at 8 DIM. Both of these models provide some resemblance to the original checkpoint, but they do not look exactly like the original checkpoint. These models are still a work in progress.

For the best results, it is recommended to use both of these LORA models at once, running CFG at 3-4 and the Sampler to DPM++ SDE Karras. This combination tends to provide a close resemblance to the original HOACB checkpoint. Although it may not be an exact match, this combination of LORA models still generate beautiful results and should be seen as an ongoing experiment.
